dct_title_s: Sketch shewing the routes of Leiutenants Conolly & Burnes
dct_description_sm: Conolly's route shown in blue; Burnes's route shown in red. Mountain passes, major deserts, and Rann of Kutch are shown. Relief shown by hachures. Routes to Yezd [Yazd] from surrounding cities are shown. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 4 (1834), pp. 278-318; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.4 1834.
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by John Murray, Albemarle Street, 1834.
